Unlike many Medieval societies, the merchants of the Lakemen function as the landed nobles and aristocrats of society. This puts them at direct odds with the Fisher's Guild, leading to an ever-present internal strife.

For the past couple centuries, the Merchants have had distinct control over society, culminating in the Master of Laketown that the Company of Thorin met. Since the downfall of the merchant Master and the rebalance of power over with the ascent of Bard I, the Fisher's guild has been demanding more and more rights, attempting to sway economic power in their favor.

Mechanically, this balance of power runs on a scale of 10 points in favor of the Merchants, to 10 points in favor of the Fisher's Guild (total range of 21 -- 10 in favor of the Merchants, 1 for a tie, and an additional 10 in favor of the Fisher's Guild). On top on a small amount of interaction with other flavor, any Burgher's Reform will move the scale 2 points in favor of the Fisher's Guild, while repealing any Burgher's Reform will move the scale 2 points in favor of the Merchants. Should the balance of power reach 8 points in favor of either side, the realm can decide to officially support that side, ending the mechanic and permanently gaining the bonuses associated with that side.

Gondor Owning the Mouths of the Entwash (

According to the canon, the Mouths of the Entwash were owned and controlled by the Kingdom of Gondor. However, that tends to cause some bordergore between Gondor and Rohan. As such, by default, the mod chooses to have Rohan own the region. Turn on this option in order to make this more lore-friendly. §RThis cannot be undone§!§I
